<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,950,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,430,1202,1228]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
This taxon was originally proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gronblad, R." box="[883,1119,1202,1229]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref8222" refString="Gronblad, R. (1945) De algis brasiliensibus. Praecipue desmidiaceis in regione inferiore fluminis Amazonas a professore August Ginzberger (Wien) anno MCMXXVII collectis. Acta Societatis Scienctiarum Fennicae 2 (6): 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="1945">Grönblad (1945: 22)</bibRefCitation>
from specimens collected in Santarém, 
<collectingRegion box="[258,375,1238,1264]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Pará State</collectingRegion>
, Amazon Basin, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gronblad" authorityYear="1945" box="[601,1131,1238,1265]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" form="mediolaeve" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="form" species="antilopaeum" variety="mamillosum">
<emphasis box="[601,774,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. antilopaeum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[833,970,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">mamillosum</emphasis>
f. 
<emphasis box="[1004,1131,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">mediolaeve</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Coute, A. &amp; Tell, G." pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 228" refId="ref7655" refString="Coute, A. &amp; Tell, G. (1981) Ultrastructure de la paroi cellulaire des desmidiacees au microscope electronique a balaiage. Beih. Nova Hedwigia 68: 1 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">Couté &amp; Tell (1981: 197)</bibRefCitation>
raised that form to a varietal level: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coute &amp; Tell" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Gronblad" box="[587,941,1274,1301]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="mamillosum" variety="mediolaeve">
<emphasis box="[587,755,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. mamillosum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[810,941,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">mediolaeve</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[941,945,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,950,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coute &amp; Tell" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Gronblad" box="[392,571,1310,1337]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="mamillosum" variety="mediolaeve">
var. 
<emphasis box="[443,571,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">mediolaeve</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the nominate variety by not having a spine in the midregion of semicells, and smallest cell dimensions (
<bibRefCitation author="Prescott, G. W. &amp; Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Vinyard, W. C." box="[583,802,1346,1372]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" refId="ref8840" refString="Prescott, G. W., Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Vinyard, W. C. (1982) A Synopsis of North American Desmids. Part II. Desmidiaceae: Placodermae. Section 4. University of Nebraska Press, Lincoln, 700 pp." type="book" year="1982">
Prescott 
<emphasis box="[681,736,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">et al.</emphasis>
1982
</bibRefCitation>
). It somewhat resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gronblad) Kurt Forster (1969: 62)" authorityName="Kurt Forster" authorityPageNumber="62" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Gronblad" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="mamillosum" variety="sexaculeatum">
<emphasis box="[1080,1246,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. mamillosum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1299,1451,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">sexaculeatum</emphasis>
(Grönblad) Kurt 
<bibRefCitation author="Forster, K." box="[326,532,1382,1409]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="5 - 116" refId="ref7977" refString="Forster, K. (1969) Amazonische Desmidieen 1. Areal Santarem. Amazoniana 2 (1 - 2): 5 - 116, pl. 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1969">Förster (1969: 62)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but this latter 
<taxonomicName box="[699,857,1382,1408]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" rank="variety" variety="differs">variety differs</taxonomicName>
by having basal angles of semicells decorated by the single spine, and a ring of pores around a central one, visible in the apical view (
<bibRefCitation author="Forster, K." box="[1036,1184,1418,1445]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="5 - 116" refId="ref7977" refString="Forster, K. (1969) Amazonische Desmidieen 1. Areal Santarem. Amazoniana 2 (1 - 2): 5 - 116, pl. 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1969">Förster 1969</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,950,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
<bibRefCitation author="Thomasson, K." box="[189,406,1454,1480]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 57" refId="ref9701" refString="Thomasson, K. (1971) Amazonian desmids. Memoires Institute Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique 86: 1 - 57." type="journal article" year="1971">Thomasson (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, studying material from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1964" box="[692,862,1454,1480]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="mamillosum">
<emphasis box="[692,862,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. mamillosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in Maica Lake (Santarém, 
<collectingRegion box="[1292,1344,1454,1480]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Pará</collectingRegion>
) and Rio Preto da Eva Lake (Rio Preto da Eva, 
<collectingRegion box="[571,694,1490,1516]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
), Amazon Basin, observed that taxa have a typical mamillate base, and some specimens have 1–2 frontal spines. The author considered that all 
<taxonomicName box="[1016,1156,1526,1552]" form="under" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" rank="form">forma under</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1964" box="[1165,1335,1526,1552]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="mamillosum">
<emphasis box="[1165,1335,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. mamillosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gronblad, R." box="[172,363,1562,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref8222" refString="Gronblad, R. (1945) De algis brasiliensibus. Praecipue desmidiaceis in regione inferiore fluminis Amazonas a professore August Ginzberger (Wien) anno MCMXXVII collectis. Acta Societatis Scienctiarum Fennicae 2 (6): 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="1945">Grönblad (1945)</bibRefCitation>
, besides 
<taxonomicName authority="Kurt Forster (1981: 247)" authorityName="Kurt Forster" authorityPageNumber="247" authorityYear="1981" box="[467,1038,1562,1589]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="canadense" variety="borgei">
<emphasis box="[467,617,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. canadense</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[675,747,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">borgei</emphasis>
Kurt 
<bibRefCitation author="Forster, K." box="[815,1038,1562,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="226 - 235" refId="ref8030" refString="Forster, K. (1981) Revision und Validierung von Desmidiaceen-Namen aus fruheren Publikationen. 1. Algological Studies / Archiv fur Hydrobiologie Supplement 28: 226 - 235." type="journal article" year="1981">Förster (1981: 247)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, are considered to belong within the morphological range of the species. Until molecular studies to be conducted to verify the delimitation of the varieties of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1964" box="[166,334,1634,1660]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="mamillosum">
<emphasis box="[166,334,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. mamillosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we consider more appropriate to maintain 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coute &amp; Tell" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Gronblad" box="[823,999,1634,1661]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="mamillosum" variety="mediolaeve">
var. 
<emphasis box="[871,999,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">mediolaeve</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,950,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
The zygospore of 
<taxonomicName box="[393,757,1670,1697]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="mammilosum" variety="mediolaeve">
<emphasis box="[393,573,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. mammilosum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[629,757,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">mediolaeve</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
analyzed resembles to format observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nordstedt" authorityYear="1870" box="[1237,1364,1670,1696]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="trilobum">
<emphasis box="[1237,1364,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. trilobum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except by absence apical furcated spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,950,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
Details of the scanning electron microscopy (
<collectionCode box="[693,754,1742,1768]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">SEM</collectionCode>
) of the 
<taxonomicName box="[838,1013,1742,1769]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="mammilosum" variety="mediolaeve">
var. 
<emphasis box="[885,1013,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">mediolaeve</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Coute, A. &amp; Tell, G." pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 228" refId="ref7655" refString="Coute, A. &amp; Tell, G. (1981) Ultrastructure de la paroi cellulaire des desmidiacees au microscope electronique a balaiage. Beih. Nova Hedwigia 68: 1 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">Couté &amp; Tell (1981: 207</bibRefCitation>
, Pl. 3, fig, 7–8), showing smooth facial semicells, punctuated cell walls, and spines with a characteristic mamillate base, similar to the specimens analyzed under photonic microscopy in the present study (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1269,1814,1841]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–30" captionStartId="4.[136,243,1901,1923]" captionTargetBox="[223,1374,227,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[201,1386,190,1876]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8–30. Bourrelyodesmus comperei sp. nov. (8–16): frontal view (8, 11, 13–16), lateral view (9), apical view (10, 12), morphological variation (13–16). Xanthidium concinnum var. longispinum var. nov. (17–24): frontal view (17, 20, 23–24), lateral view (18, 21), apical view (19, 22), morphological variation (23–24). Xanthidium mamillosum var. mediolaeve (25–30): frontal view (25, 28), empty cell after reproduction (26), zygospore (27), lateral view (29), apical view (30). Scale Bar: 10 μm, except Fig. 25, 28–30 (40 μm), Fig. 26–27 (50 μm, horizontal bar)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6331882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6331882/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Figs. 25, 28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,950,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
